<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF850A5DF84EFDFDF85B" box="[284,589,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Mesoconius auristrigatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F68FF850918F84DFCACF85B" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[601,796,1933,1959]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, external characters. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF850F63F84DFB87F85B" bold="true" box="[1058,1079,1933,1959]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF850F0AF84DFBD0F85B" bold="true" box="[1099,1120,1933,1959]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C</emphasis>
. Living ♀♀, Ecuador. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF850BFCF870FF61F836" bold="true" box="[189,209,1968,1994]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">B</emphasis>
. Head, ♀. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF850A11F870FED5F836" bold="true" box="[336,357,1968,1994]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">D</emphasis>
. Holotype, ♀, MNBG. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F68FF85093AF870FD3FF836" bold="true" box="[635,655,1968,1994]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E</emphasis>
. Pleuron and base of abdomen to show orange katatergite.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F69FF8B0BFCFECCFAC7FE73" blockId="23.[189,1399,267,435]" lastBlockId="24.[189,1399,265,399]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840BFCFECCFEAFFEDA" allCaps="true" box="[189,287,268,294]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">THORAX.</emphasis>
Cervical sclerite with a vertical groove separating a large subquadrate posterior portion from a small anterior portion. Notum finely and densely microtrichose, acrostichal and dorsocentral setulae in distinct rows, scattered setulae also present anterolaterally. Postpronotal lobe dull, densely microtrichose with several scattered small pale setae, anterior margin bare, shiny and almost vertical, posterior margin bare and sloped. Notopleuron with two widely spaced bristles, posterior bristle darker and thicker than anterior. Dorsocentral bristle very small, golden, shorter than scutellar length and about ⅓ as long as golden supra-alar. Scutellum with four small discal setulae and a pair of long, closely spaced black apical bristles (longer than scutellum). Katatergite very prominent, with a long, nipple-like microtrichose pointed process. Vertical row of katepisternal bristles golden. All coxae with golden anteroventral setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0DC4AB6F69FF840BFCF8A6FC06F816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3401913/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" startId="23.[189,232,1894,1920]" targetBox="[189,1398,478,1863]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F69FF840BFCF8A6FC06F816" blockId="23.[189,1399,1894,2027]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840BFCF8A6FEBDF87C" bold="true" box="[189,269,1894,1920]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 6.</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F69FF840A59F8A7FCA1F87D" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[280,785,1894,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="auristrigatus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="Mesoconius auristrigatus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F69FF840A59F8A7FCA1F87D" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[280,785,1894,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auristrigatus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840A59F8A7FDF6F87C" box="[280,582,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mesoconius auristrigatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F69FF840910F8A6FCA1F87D" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[593,785,1894,1921]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, internal characters. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840F4DF8A6FB91F87C" bold="true" box="[1036,1057,1894,1920]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A</emphasis>
. Male epandrium and cerci, posterodorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840AE8F84AFE0DF858" bold="true" box="[425,445,1930,1956]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">B</emphasis>
. Spermathecae and associated structures. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF8408ECF849FC72F85F" bold="true" box="[941,962,1929,1955]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. Male terminalia with phallus teased out, directed ventrally. 
<emphasis id="B90648316F69FF840A92F86DFE58F83B" bold="true" box="[467,488,1965,1991]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">D</emphasis>
. Apex of abdomen, ♂, lateral view. Abbreviations: c = cercus; ddp = distal distiphallus; e = epandrium; hy = hypandrium; pb = phallic bulb.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F66FF8B0BFCFE6FFB9BFE11" blockId="24.[189,1399,431,493]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0BFCFE6FFE82FE35" allCaps="true" box="[189,306,431,457]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">ABDOMEN.</emphasis>
Abdominal segment 1 and basal half of segment 2 petiolate; length of 1+2 slightly less than double length of tergite 3. T1 setose, with preapical long, thin lateral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F66FF8B0BFCFDCCFB4BFCC3" blockId="24.[189,1399,524,832]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0BFCFDCCFE3BFDDA" allCaps="true" box="[189,395,524,550]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">FEMALE ABDOMEN.</emphasis>
Oviscape bare, except for scattered setulae. Bursa small, suboval, ventral receptacle small and inconspicuous. Single spermathecal duct constricted at base, branching off a very short common duct that then tapers slightly to much longer paired spermathecal duct, which is divided into distinct parts including a short rugose basal ⅓ that abruptly transforms into a slightly narrower, relatively smooth (indistinctly striate) distal ⅔. Paired spermathecae expanded distally, apex invaginated, surface reticulate, stem (beyond division of paired duct) broad, conspicuously coiled and finely tuberculate on basal half, distal half dark, thick and very strongly tuberculate. Single spermathecal duct similar in texture to distal part of paired spermathecal duct but much smaller, single spermatheca small, on a thick tuberculate stem as thick as spermatheca, separated from main part of duct by a constriction.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F66FF8B0BFCFCA0FC51FB6F" blockId="24.[189,1399,863,1171]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">MALE ABDOMEN (tentative association; see Remarks). Sternites 5and 6large, tapered anteriorly and notched posteromedially. Synsternite 7–8 sparsely microtrichose, shiny, contrasting with dull, microtrichose preceding sclerites and pale microtrichose epandrium; S7 with a very broad but unmodified ventral part. Sternite 8 much smaller than epandrium, epandrium elongate, sparsely setose except for a dense patch of setae posteroventrally; cercus prominent, large, elongate and slightly curved, strongly projecting posteroventrally. Hypandrium elongate and slender, extending to anterior margin of T6. Basiphallus small, not extending beyond base of distiphallus. Basal part of distiphallus narrow basally, distally abruptly expanding to enclose a small phallic bulb; distal part of distiphallus tapered and whip-like. Ejaculatory apodeme very small, smaller than attached sperm pump.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368C7A86F66FF8B0BFCFB73FB11F9C5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F66FF8B0BFCFB73FE9FFB31" blockId="24.[189,303,1203,1229]" box="[189,303,1203,1229]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading id="D085234F6F66FF8B0BFCFB73FE9FFB31" bold="true" box="[189,303,1203,1229]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0BFCFB73FE9FFB31" bold="true" box="[189,303,1203,1229]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F66FF8B0BFCFB22FB11F9C5" blockId="24.[189,1399,1249,1593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B0BFCFB22FE58FB07" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,488,1250,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auristrigatus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0BFCFB22FE58FB07" box="[189,488,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Mesoconius auristrigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be very closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B08C2FB22FB8DFB07" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[899,1085,1249,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripleuron" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B08C2FB22FB8DFB07" box="[899,1085,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. nigripleuron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F66FF8B0F05FB22FB2DFB00" box="[1092,1181,1250,1276]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F66FF8B0FACFB22FA98FB00" box="[1261,1320,1250,1276]" name="Peru" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Peru</collectingCountry>
). Male specimens assigned to these two species are similar, but those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B08F9FAC5FBC2FAE3" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[952,1138,1285,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripleuron" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B08F9FAC5FBC2FAE3" box="[952,1138,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. nigripleuron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F66FF8B0F38FAC5FB64FAE3" box="[1145,1236,1285,1311]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have apically concave or bilobed cerci, in contrast to the tapered cerci of the one male treated as 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B0FEFFAE9FAC0FABE" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1198,1392,1321,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auristrigatus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0FEFFAE9FAC0FABE" box="[1198,1392,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. auristrigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These species also differ in leg colour and spermathecal structure, and they are widely separated (p-distance ca 10%) on the CO1 tree (
<figureCitation id="134988A66F66FF8B09C8FAAEFD53FA75" box="[649,739,1390,1417]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="123.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1373,810,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@123.[189,1398,799,1896]" captionTargetPageId="123" captionText="Fig. 50. Maximum likelihood tree from CO1 barcodes. Sequences were aligned using BOLD (amino acid based HMM) and then manually corrected. Maximum likelihood analysis was performed in RAxML (ver. 8.2) using GTR-G with 100 replicates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3402003/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Ecuadorian and Colombian female specimens treated here as 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B0A56FA52FE66FA57" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[279,470,1426,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auristrigatus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B0A56FA52FE66FA57" box="[279,470,1426,1451]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. auristrigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have distinct CO1 sequences and differ slightly in the colour of the margins of the bands on mid and hind tibia. Examination of more extensive collections might justify recognition of the Ecuadorian populations as a separate species and might show that the Ecuadorian populations on the eastern side of the Central Valley (now known from one male) and western side of the Central Valley (now known only from females) differ. See also Remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F66FF8B08F1F9DFFB8FF9C4" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[944,1087,1567,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noteques" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F66FF8B08F1F9DFFB8FF9C4" box="[944,1087,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">M. noteques</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F66FF8B0F07F9DFFB11F9C5" box="[1094,1185,1567,1593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
